1
00:01:59,479 --> 00:02:00,540
What are you doing?

2
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,720
Is this fun?

3
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,800
I don't know what you are talking about.

4
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,200
Move. Don't block my way.

5
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,850
I'm asking you. Is this fun?

6
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,920
Don't you know if it's fun?

7
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,120
I didn't slander you.

8
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,400
Was I wrong?

9
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:21,960
Xiong Yuanbao.

10
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,520
Are you afraid of others exposing your faults

11
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,079
and calling you an orphan?

12
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,700
What are you doing?

13
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:40,440
What's going on?

14
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,210
It seems Qiao Yan brought up

15
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,880
Yuanbao's parents first.

16
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:56,560
Mu Qingyun.

17
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:02,300
What are you doing? Tearing down the classroom?

18
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:08,800
You just wait.

19
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:12,120
Mu Qingyun. Mu Qingyun. Mu Qingyun.

20
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:18,600
Yuanbao.

21
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,610
Don't come over.

22
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,440
Yuanbao,

23
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,200
listen to me.

24
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,720
I really didn't mean to

25
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,720
tell Mr. Men about your background.

26
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,800
Please don't do anything foolish.

27
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,440
I just...

28
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,280
Mutou,

29
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,560
they are right.

30
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:36,400
Since I was little, everyone has said the same.

31
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,680
I am an orphan,

32
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,920
a wild child with no parents.

33
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,360
Yes, I am scared.

34
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,079
But being scared

35
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,520
doesn't mean I need others' pity.

36
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,680
Xiong Yuanbao,

37
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,560
how can you say you are

38
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,890
an unwanted wild child?

39
00:03:52,079 --> 00:03:53,000
You have your grandmother

40
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,800
and me.

41
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,520
My parents are your parents.

42
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,730
Whether you admit it or not,

43
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,040
it is the truth.

44
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:00,880
I know this

45
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,360
has always been a wound in your heart,

46
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,890
untouchable and unspoken.

47
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,360
But you can't live your whole life

48
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:05,960
like an ostrich,

49
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,960
burying your head in the sand

50
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,620
and refusing to look forward.

51
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,960
If your grandmother knew you were like this,

52
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,240
how sad would she be?

53
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,620
Think about it,

54
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,279
she can look forward with optimism and grace.

55
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,560
Why can't you live in the sun?

56
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:34,840
Yuanbao.

57
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,460
What are you doing?

58
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,690
Yuanbao, promise me first.

59
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,480
No matter what difficulties you face in the future,

60
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,159
don't ever think about taking your own life.

61
00:04:54,159 --> 00:04:55,440
If something happens to you,

62
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,440
how can I explain it to Grandma?

63
00:04:58,159 --> 00:04:59,960
Who wants to take their own life?

64
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:03,560
Didn't you tell me to live towards the sun?

65
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,800
I'm just feeling the breeze and the sunshine.

66
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,680
Okay?

67
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,200
Seriously.

68
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:17,000
You really didn't think that?

69
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,880
No.

70
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,680
Then let's hurry back.

71
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,040
Come on, I'll carry you.

72
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,720
Why?

73
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,850
This way we look more imposing.

74
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,000
What happened to you two?

75
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,600
Yuanbao, are you okay?

76
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,360
I'm fine.

77
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,120
Go back to your seats.

78
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,680
Class.

79
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,640
Taking the opportunity of this class meeting,

80
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,840
I'd like to apologize to Xiong Yuanbao.

81
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,400
Yuanbao.

82
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,240
I was too impulsive today.

83
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,080
I blamed you without finding out the truth.

84
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:07,280
I didn't think it through,

85
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,800
and acted unfairly.

86
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,890
But teachers are human too,

87
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,400
and we make mistakes.

88
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,120
So right here,

89
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,360
I sincerely apologize to you.

90
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,680
It's fine, teacher.

91
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,200
Qiao Yan.

92
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,040
I talked too much.

93
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,800
I shouldn't have talked behind your back

94
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,120
and said so many mean things.

95
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:39,680
I hope you won't take it to heart.

96
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,840
I'm sorry.

97
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,000
Being in the same class

98
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,640
is a great destiny.

99
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,920
I hope

100
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,980
you can cherish this destiny.

101
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,360
Shake hands and make up.

102
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:57,360
Then we need a friendly hug.

103
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:00,040
Right, let's hug.

104
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,040
Yes.

105
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,800
Yes, exactly.

106
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:18,040
It doesn't feel good to be talked about behind your back, does it?

107
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,560
Let's go. School is over.

108
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,659
Stop fighting.

109
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,200
Yuanbao.

110
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,320
I know you're suffering.

111
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,040
I'll always be with you.

112
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,020
My sweet daughter.

113
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,720
My sweet daughter, over here.

114
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,520
Yuanbao.

115
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:03,720
Come here.

116
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,600
Yuanbao.

117
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:09,010
You called them?

118
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,480
Why are you just standing there? Go.

119
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,240
Yuanbao, we're here to pick you up from school.

120
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,760
107.

121
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,200
108.

122
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,600
109.

123
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,320
The competition is on Yuanbao's birthday.

124
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,720
Such a special day.

125
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,920
What can 109 do?

126
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,120
My mom is so stingy.

127
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,160
Mom and Dad.

128
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,360
I'm going to Shanghai again.

129
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,840
And it happens to be on my birthday.

130
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:09,600
Did you arrange all of this?

131
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,170
May the trip to Shanghai

132
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,520
be smooth

133
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,960
and safe.

134
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,930
I must win the award.

135
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,220
Xiong Yuanbao,

136
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,720
you can do it!

137
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,450
Second interview site.

138
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,280
New thinking, new expression, real experience.

139
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:29,010
New thinking, new expression, real experience.

140
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,960
Thank you for just now.

141
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,320
Anyone else would have done the same.

142
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,200
I'm waiting for a car here, so I don't need the umbrella.

143
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,060
The rain might get heavier later.

144
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,720
Take it and go home quickly.

145
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,720
Thank you.

146
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,840
But I'm not a local.

147
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:43,890
I just came to Shanghai yesterday for a competition.

148
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,680
How about you leave me your contact info?

149
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,280
I'll return the umbrella to you then.

150
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,040
No need.

151
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,560
Wait a moment.

152
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:56,680
Brother.

153
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,480
Why did it take you so long to answer?

154
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,540
I thought something happened to you.

155
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:01,960
Me?

156
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,760
I'm at a bus stop near the exam center,

157
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,420
taking shelter from the rain.

158
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,320
Then I'll wait for you.

159
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,720
Call me when you get here.

160
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,860
You don't need to return the umbrella. I'm leaving.

161
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,960
How can I just take your umbrella for nothing?

162
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,600
No.

163
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,360
Give me your contact info,

164
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,760
or your address.

165
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,240
I'll mail it back to you.

166
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:30,880
I'll be going now.

167
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,760
Thank you!

168
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:35,800
Wait.

169
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:37,480
What is it?

170
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,960
Watch out for cars.

171
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,480
Yuanbao.

172
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:58,520
Why are you so late? I've been waiting for a long time.

173
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,600
Sorry, sorry.

174
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,240
Exam is over. How was it?

175
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,740
I almost didn't make it in.

176
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,530
As long as you took the exam, it's fine.

177
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,080
What was the topic?

178
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:13,080
I wrote about my parents.

179
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,690
Let's go. I'll take you to a good place.

180
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,800
Since we're here,

181
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,400
whatever you want to play or eat,

182
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,440
just tell me.

183
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,320
Like roller coasters

184
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,520
or something.

185
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,720
Keep bragging.

186
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,540
Aren't you afraid of heights?

187
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,410
That was when I was a kid.

188
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,360
I am not afraid of anything now.

189
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,760
Just watch my performance later.

190
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,720
Hold on to me if you're scared,

191
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,480
got it?

192
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,280
Don't say I know you.

193
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:37,720
Yuanbao,

194
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,240
I thought you would be touched by the scene

195
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,120
and think of your parents.

196
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,980
That was the last birthday

197
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:49,080
they spent with me in this life.

198
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,880
I was quite anxious before coming here.

199
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,840
I thought I would be afraid

200
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,440
and resistant.

201
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:01,880
But after coming here,

202
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,020
I feel much more relieved.

203
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,920
Thank you, Mutou.

204
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,800
No need to be polite with me.

205
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:11,840
Didn't you say

206
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,600
that we are like

207
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,520
biological sisters?

208
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,200
Shouldn't sisters

209
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,200
share through thick and thin?

210
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,560
Before, when I said we were sisters,

211
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:24,600
you always said we were brothers.

212
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:27,800
Why admit you're a beauty today?

213
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,240
Come on.

214
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,320
Since it's your birthday,

215
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:40,000
sister, don't push your luck.

216
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,280
Wait a second.

217
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,400
I ran too fast just now.

218
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,040
It's a sense of ritual.

219
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:09,970
Sense of ritual.

220
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,320
I couldn't find candles.

221
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,980
I'll use a glow stick instead.

222
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:17,800
Come on, make a wish.

223
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:22,240
Mom and Dad.

224
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,520
I'm at the amusement park for my birthday again.

225
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:26,280
Mutou is with me this time.

226
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,760
Do you see?

227
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,440
Yuanbao, send me some messages.

228
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,580
To give me courage.

229
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,280
My mom signed me up for cram school.

230
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,840
The teacher kept us late today.

231
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:44,920
It's a bit dark on the road.

232
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,720
And I'm a little scared walking home alone.

233
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:48,120
Ruirui, don't be afraid.

234
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,080
I'm with you.

235
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,120
Be safe by yourself.

236
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:53,720
Let me know immediately if anything happens.

237
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,800
Okay, I'll let you know when I arrive.

238
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,920
I feel much better talking to you.

239
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:00,170
You really are my little sunshine.

240
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:24,680
Don't be afraid.

241
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,880
I'm right beside you.

242
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,650
They won't dare to do anything.

243
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,360
What's wrong?

244
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,720
It's nothing.

245
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,040
It's not safe for a girl to walk at night.

246
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,540
Don't take the small alleys anymore.

247
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,680
Gong Yu.

248
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:16,840
Well.

249
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,440
Let's go.

250
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,000
How much were these green beans?

251
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,880
Three-fifty a catty. What about yours?

252
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:19,960
Mine were three.

253
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,680
Yours were cheaper, Mrs. Xiong.

254
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:22,440
They're pretty good.

255
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,720
Yeah, very fresh.

256
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,010
I also bought these.

257
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,840
Mrs. Wang, Mrs. Xiong.

258
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,280
Just got back from grocery shopping?

259
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:31,560
Hey, Li.

260
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,800
Your scarf is exactly like mine.

261
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,520
It really is.

262
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,200
My son heard

263
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,680
that buying mom a red scarf this year

264
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,800
will bring her health and longevity.

265
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:43,640
Look.

266
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:46,160
He even insisted I wear it.

267
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,680
My daughter said the same thing.

268
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:49,800
That shows

269
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,960
your kids care about you.

270
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,340
You should be content.

271
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,040
Content? How could I not be?

272
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:58,520
Well, you guys keep chatting.

273
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,980
I have something to do, so I'll get going.

274
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,840
What we just said,

275
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,760
did she take it the wrong way?

276
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:12,560
If Mrs. Xiong's son were still around,

277
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:14,520
he would have bought her one too.

278
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:18,000
It's a little pricier.

279
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Because the material is good,

280
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,840
the original price was ninety-nine.

281
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,040
Now it's fifty.

282
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,240
What about this one?

283
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,000
The thin one.

284
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,970
Ma'am, listen to me.

285
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,840
The original price of this thin one is fifty.

286
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:28,770
Now it's thirty.

287
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:33,720
Thirty is enough.

288
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,800
Just thirty.

289
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:35,520
Thirty for this.

290
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:36,480
I can't do thirty.

291
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:37,920
I'd be losing money at thirty.

292
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,380
It's the wholesale price.

293
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:46,200
Try it on.

294
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,720
You guys try it on and see.

295
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:58,400
Grandma.

296
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:00,980
Are you hungry?

297
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,200
I'll cook right away.

298
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,440
We'll eat soon.

299
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,800
Grandma.

300
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,040
Didn't they say

301
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,400
giving Mom a red scarf this year

302
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,090
would bring her health and a long life?

303
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:38,440
I dreamed of my dad yesterday.

304
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:41,920
He asked me to give you

305
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,640
a brand-new red scarf on his behalf.

306
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,960
Offer one to your mom too.

307
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,920
Your mom loved red the most.

308
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:04,600
Grandma, come here.

309
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:11,680
Look.

310
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,480
Grandma, I'm

311
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,680
a little late.

312
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,600
I also bought you a red scarf.

313
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,080
Okay.

314
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,380
Put them both on. It's double the effect.

315
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,840
I'll wear them both.

316
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,000
Auntie Wenying,

317
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:38,000
try it on.

318
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:43,340
I thought I could give you a surprise.

319
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,800
I'll wear them all.

320
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:48,680
I'll put them all on.

321
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,360
It looks beautiful, Grandma.

322
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,960
Mom, I bought this one for you.

323
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,240
Put it on.

324
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,360
I have one too?

325
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,560
Of course.

326
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:58,080
Here, child.

327
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,640
You wear it too.

328
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,170
Thank you, Grandma.

329
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,080
Here.

330
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,040
Put one on Yuanbao too.

331
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,500
Put one on our Yuanbao too.

332
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,160
Thank you, Grandma.

333
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,800
We're all happy.

334
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,080
Right, to celebrate Yuanbao

335
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,560
winning the essay contest,

336
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:14,280
Auntie bought you pig trotters and ribs.

337
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:17,240
Grandma.

338
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,120
Mom.

339
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,520
This brat, really.

340
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,240
The kids have grown up.

341
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,740
They are sensible now.

342
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,520
Yuanbao won a prize in the essay contest.

343
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:47,400
Tiejun and Aihua can finally rest in peace.

344
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:48,760
Yes.

345
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,000
For the kids,

346
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,520
you've taken on so many part-time jobs.

347
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:55,770
You've worked hard.

348
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:56,880
Not at all.

349
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:01,680
This way, we owe them a little less.

350
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:03,920
Owe?

351
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,080
Alright.

352
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,960
Don't dwell on it.

353
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:15,000
That very night,

354
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,800
after I sent you the message,

355
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,960
I was walking alone on the path home.

356
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,760
The situation was tense.

357
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,360
There were a few delinquents

358
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,520
whistling at me.

359
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,240
He

360
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,840
suddenly appeared behind me.

361
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,200
He escorted me through that

362
00:24:29,320 --> 00:24:31,960
most dangerous and darkest road.

363
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:35,080
But the situation was so urgent at the time.

364
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,160
I was terrified.

365
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,080
I didn't even ask for his contact information.

366
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:41,120
I only heard someone call him,

367
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:42,240
Gong Yu.

368
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,850
Don't you think it's frustrating?

369
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:46,760
Right.

370
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:54,600
Oh no. It got smudged by the rain.

371
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:57,200
How am I supposed to return his umbrella?

372
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:59,360
Who is it? Someone new?

373
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,400
A guy or a girl?

374
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,540
It was after that essay competition.

375
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,280
It suddenly started raining.

376
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,000
Then I almost got hit by a car.

377
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,580
And suddenly a guy appeared and saved me.

378
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,640
He even gave me his umbrella.

379
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,120
I just want his contact info

380
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,800
and return the umbrella to him.

381
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:16,200
Oh my.

382
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,840
This is more like an idol drama than my life.

383
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,080
Is he handsome?

384
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,920
A little bit. He looks like Aaron Kwok.

385
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:25,400
Aaron Kwok?

386
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:32,200
Oh my.

387
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:35,160
You must be regretting it so much.

388
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,640
It's fine.

389
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:41,320
It's just that I can't return his umbrella.

390
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:42,520
Will he think

391
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,360
that I don't keep my word?

392
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,400
Here, why don't you leave the umbrella with me?

393
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:50,600
So you won't get upset looking at it.

394
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:57,920
Oh my.

395
00:25:58,280 --> 00:26:00,320
This is your favorite Hu Ge sticker.

396
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,520
Best friends share everything.

397
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,760
Give me the notebook.

398
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:10,160
Are you sure this is okay?

399
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,800
It does look a bit weird.

400
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:19,440
Forget it.

401
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:20,960
Let's just go with it.

402
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:23,000
When I want to see the whole face,

403
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:26,100
I'll come to you to piece it together.

404
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,800
When you met that guy,

405
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,760
how did you feel?

406
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:41,840
It's a feeling deep in your heart.

407
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:46,480
It's like this person is braving the wind

408
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,440
and coming just for you.

409
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:51,200
You start to frequently

410
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:54,320
and involuntarily think about it.

411
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,360
You're done, bro.

412
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,240
You've fallen.

413
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:10,850
What is this?

414
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:13,140
Self-Cultivation of Charming Boys.

415
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,140
What are you doing?

416
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,280
Why aren't ours growing?

417
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:26,480
I don't know either.

418
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,040
Maybe we should eat more papaya.

419
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:30,480
By the way.

420
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:34,720
This is

421
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:37,000
the latest magazine my dad brought back

422
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:38,800
from his business trip to Guangzhou.

423
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:41,440
It's full of the most popular clothes,

424
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:43,360
makeup, and hairstyles right now.

425
00:27:43,360 --> 00:27:44,840
This is good. This is good.

426
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:46,080
This is good.

427
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,920
Why does this look...

428
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:51,980
It looks a bit like a delinquent girl.

429
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,520
This is good. Long hair, short hair.

430
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:55,720
This suits us.

431
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:59,360
I didn't give all my New Year's money to my mom.

432
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,000
Let's go. Hurry up.

433
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,040
What's with this look?

434
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,160
Does it look good?

435
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,720
Ruirui forced me to do it.

436
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:39,640
I still think

437
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,410
your previous look was better.

438
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:46,130
Then I'll go wash it off.

439
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,520
Luckily it's temporary.

440
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,320
Saying I'd turn into a princess.

441
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,480
It's all a lie.

442
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,740
You care so much about my opinion.

443
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:57,240
Are you trying to get my attention?

444
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,560
Is it okay now?

445
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:30,640
I'm talking to you.

446
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:35,690
Isn't it the same as before?

447
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,260
What's wrong with my face?

448
00:29:44,520 --> 00:29:46,440
Forget it. It's hopeless.

449
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,280
Crazy.

450
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,080
The floor is slippery.

451
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:17,010
Be careful when you walk next time.

452
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,400
I'm leaving first.

453
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,720
Mu Qingjun.

454
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:40,640
Stand up.

455
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:44,680
Hello, teacher.

456
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,810
Hello, students. Please sit down.

457
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:50,280
Today,

458
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:52,120
we have a new student transferring to our class.

459
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:54,520
Let's welcome him with a round of applause.

460
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,160
Mr. Tian, is there anything wrong?

461
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,200
I'm fine. Are you?

462
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,600
You went to the wrong class.

463
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,480
Sorry.

464
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:25,120
What are you all laughing at?

465
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:26,560
You two, come in.

466
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,720
This is so unreal.

467
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,800
He actually transferred to our class.

468
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:49,040
Is God finally awake?
